# To add a user, use the following command
# The -m flag adds a home directory for the user. The -c flag is essentially a comment but it is primarily used for adding the first and last name of the user. The last argument is the user ID.

useradd -m -c "FirstName LastName" user1

# To add a passwword for the user, use the following command
# This prompts you to type a password for a specific user.

passwd user1
